%TUTORIAL ------------------ IPCS - Literal Value ---------------------
%Command ===>_ZCMD
%
%                         General Values~(continued)
~A picture string:
%P'p...'~
~Picture strings allow you to enter the type of string to be found inste
~the exact characters to be found. Each character "p" can be:
~                          blank × A-Z, a-z × 0-9
~or it can be a symbol used to represent a class of characters:
~        =  any character                   .  invalid characters
~        @  alphabetic characters           -  non-numeric characters
~        #  numeric characters              <  lower case alphabetics
~        $  special characters              >  upper case alphabetics
~        ^  non-blank characters
~
~A text string:
%T't...'~
~Text strings are phrases without regard to case. Either upper or lower
~processed. Use of text strings results in either an equal or unequal co
~
~A hexadecimal string:
%X'xx...'~hexadecimal (1-256 digits, optionally separated by blanks or c
)END
